<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12491&amp;p=142972#p142972</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12491&amp;p=142972#p142972"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Nintendulator extremely slow!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12491&amp;p=142972#p142972"><![CDATA[
Most emulators will show you this.  I recommend trying the following:<br /><br />- FCEUX (get one of the SVN builds; EmuCR offers them)<br />- VirtuaNES<br />- NO$NES (a little finicky, but offers some convenience debugging-esque things that I haven't seen in other emulators (no I will not discuss them here, please stay focused/on topic))<br /><br />FCEUX offers &quot;refresh sliders&quot; on most of the debugging windows, to allow you to refresh more often or less often depending on what you want.<br /><br />I make no promises that any of these will do what you need exclusively, or work better than Nintendulator.  You'll need to try them out.  I myself do development using the above emulators, Nintendulator, and Nestopia as well (not for debugging but just general testing).  Once I have something that seems right, I try it out on actual hardware with a PowerPak.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Fri Mar 13, 2015 5:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
